<item>
            <title>[JDK-8328037] Test java/util/Formatter/Padding.java has unnecessary high heap requirement after JDK-8326718</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8328037</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8326718&quot; title=&quot;Test java/util/Formatter/Padding.java should timeout on large inputs before fix in JDK-8299677&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8326718&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8326718&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added a few cases to test java/util/Formatter/Padding.java with huge Strings as arguments. Since all possible argument combinations for the test are stored in one array, nothing can be garbage collected while the test is running and the heap requirement is blown up.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
In one of our test pipelines we run tier1 tests with VMs that default to 384M of heap and this is not sufficient any longer.</description>
